{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.40",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 40,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 40 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:1",
      "text": "Great travail is created for every man. A heavy yoke is upon the sons of Adam, from the day of their coming forth from their mother’s womb, until the day for their burial in the mother of all things.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:2",
      "text": "The expectation of things to come, and the day of death, trouble their thoughts, and cause fear in their hearts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:3",
      "text": "From him who sits on a throne of glory, even to him who is humbled in earth and ashes,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:4",
      "text": "from him who wears purple and a crown, even to him who is clothed in burlap,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:5",
      "text": "there is wrath, jealousy, trouble, unrest, fear of death, anger, and strife. In the time of rest upon his bed, his night sleep changes his knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:6",
      "text": "He gets little or no rest, and afterward in his sleep, as in a day of keeping watch, he is troubled in the vision of his heart, as one who has escaped from the front of battle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:7",
      "text": "In the very time of his deliverance, he awakens, and marvels that the fear is nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:8",
      "text": "To all creatures, human and animal, and upon sinners sevenfold more,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:9",
      "text": "come death, bloodshed, strife, sword, calamities, famine, suffering, and plague.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:10",
      "text": "All these things were created for the wicked, and because of them the flood came.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:11",
      "text": "All things that are of the earth turn to the earth again. All things that are of the waters return into the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:12",
      "text": "All bribery and injustice will be blotted out. Good faith will stand forever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:13",
      "text": "The goods of the unjust will be dried up like a river, and like a great thunder in rain will go off in noise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:14",
      "text": "In opening his hands, a man will be made glad; so lawbreakers will utterly fail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:15",
      "text": "The children of the ungodly won’t grow many branches, and are as unhealthy roots on a sheer rock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:16",
      "text": "The reeds by every water or river bank will be plucked up before all grass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:17",
      "text": "Kindness is like a garden of blessings. Almsgiving endures forever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:18",
      "text": "The life of one who labors and is content will be made sweet. He who finds a treasure is better than both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:19",
      "text": "Children and the building of a city establish a name. A blameless wife is better than both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:20",
      "text": "Wine and music rejoice the heart. The love of wisdom is better than both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:21",
      "text": "The pipe and the lute make pleasant melody. A pleasant tongue is better than both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:22",
      "text": "Your eye desires grace and beauty, but the green shoots of grain more than both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:23",
      "text": "A friend and a companion is always welcome, and a wife with her husband is better than both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:24",
      "text": "Relatives and helpers are for a time of affliction, but almsgiving rescues better than both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:25",
      "text": "Gold and silver will make the foot stand sure, and counsel is esteemed better than both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:26",
      "text": "Riches and strength will lift up the heart. The fear of the Lord is better than both. There is nothing lacking in the fear of the Lord. In it, there is no need to seek help.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:27",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is like a garden of blessing and covers a man more than any glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:28",
      "text": "My son, don’t lead a beggar’s life. It is better to die than to beg.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:29",
      "text": "A man who looks to the table of another, his life is not to be considered a life. He will pollute his soul with another person’s food, but a wise and well-instructed person will beware of that.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.40.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 40:30",
      "text": "Begging will be sweet in the mouth of the shameless, but it kindles a fire in his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
